  "prompt": "What are the recipes of five minutes easy to make snacks?",
  "response": "Here are five quick and easy snack recipes that you can make in just five minutes:\n\n### 1. **Avocado Toast**\n- **Ingredients**: 1 slice of bread, \u00bd ripe avocado, salt, pepper, optional toppings (chili flakes, lemon juice, or drizzle of olive oil).\n- **Instructions**: Toast the bread. Mash the avocado in a bowl, season with salt and pepper, and spread it on the toast. Add optional toppings and enjoy!\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Microwave Mug Omelette**\n- **Ingredients**: 2 eggs, 2 tablespoons milk, salt, pepper, shredded cheese, and optional add-ins (chopped veggies, ham, or herbs).\n- **Instructions**: Whisk eggs, milk, salt, and pepper in a microwave-safe mug. Stir in cheese and other add-ins. Microwave for 1\u20132 minutes, checking until fully cooked.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Yogurt Parfait**\n- **Ingredients**: \u00bd cup Greek yogurt, \u00bc cup granola, \u00bc cup fresh fruit (berries, banana, etc.), drizzle of honey.\n- **Instructions**: Layer yogurt, granola, and fruit in a bowl or glass. Drizzle with honey and enjoy!\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Peanut Butter Banana Wrap**\n- **Ingredients**: 1 tortilla, 2 tablespoons peanut butter, \u00bd banana (sliced), drizzle of honey (optional).\n- **Instructions**: Spread peanut butter on the tortilla, add banana slices, and drizzle honey if desired. Roll it up and slice into bite-sized pieces if preferred.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Cheese and Crackers with Fruit**\n- **Ingredients**: Crackers, slices of cheese (like cheddar or brie), and fresh fruit (grapes, apple slices, or berries).\n- **Instructions**: Arrange crackers, cheese, and fruit on a plate for a quick and balanced snack.\n\nThese snacks are simple, nutritious, and perfect for when you\u2019re in a hurry!",
